Inside "entity X { ... }" you may only list: fieldName FieldType [validations].
INVALID (ER / UML words inside the entity — cause MismatchedTokenException on closing }):
  category Category oneToOne
  orderLines OrderLine manyToMany
  id Auto
RIGHT: declare scalar fields only, then use top-level relationship blocks.
Example WRONG entity body:
  entity Product {
    id Auto
    category Category oneToOne
  }
Example RIGHT (split):
  entity Product {
    name String required
    price BigDecimal required
  }
  entity Category {
    name String required
  }
  relationship ManyToOne {
    Product{category} to Category{product}
  }

Every entity referenced in a relationship { A{b} to B{a} } must exist in the same file (e.g. define Customer before Order{customer} to Customer).

PROMPT (example user intent): JHipster monolith JWT; Blog with title slug publishedAt; Post belongs to Blog; Comment on Post with authorName and body.

VALID JDL (manually checked shape; extend with application { } if needed):
entity Blog {
  title String required
  slug String unique
  publishedAt LocalDate
}
entity Post {
  title String required
  slug String unique
  body TextBlob
  publishedAt LocalDate
  blog Blog required
}
entity Comment {
  authorName String required
  body TextBlob
  post Post required
}
relationship ManyToOne {
  Post{blog required} to Blog{post}
  Comment{post required} to Post{comment}
}

PROMPT (example): Monolith; Product, Category, Customer, Order with status enum, OrderLine with quantity and unitPrice; relations without ER words inside entities.

VALID JDL:
entity Category {
  name String required
}
entity Product {
  name String required
  price BigDecimal required
  stock Integer required
}
entity Customer {
  name String required
}
enum OrderStatus {
  PENDING,
  PAID,
  SHIPPED
}
entity Order {
  status OrderStatus required
}
entity OrderLine {
  quantity Integer required
  unitPrice BigDecimal required
}
relationship ManyToOne {
  Product{category} to Category{product}
  Order{customer} to Customer{order}
  OrderLine{order} to Order{orderLine}
  OrderLine{product} to Product{orderLine}
}
paginate Order, Product with pagination

PROMPT (example): Authors and Books with many-to-many.

VALID JDL:
entity Author {
  name String required
  birthDate LocalDate
}
entity Book {
  title String required
  isbn String unique
  publicationDate LocalDate
}
relationship ManyToMany {
  Author{book} to Book{author}
}

Declare with: relationship RelationshipType { FromEntity{fieldName} to ToEntity{fieldName} [with javadoc("...")] }
Types: OneToMany, ManyToOne, ManyToMany, OneToOne.
Example:
relationship ManyToOne {
  Order{customer} to Customer
}
relationship OneToMany {
  Customer{order} to Order{customer}
}
ManyToMany uses join entity or implicit mapping depending on generator; prefer explicit owning side field names.

Optional top-level block:
application {
  config {
    baseName myapp
    applicationType monolith
    packageName com.example
    authenticationType jwt
    databaseType sql
    devDatabaseType h2Disk
    prodDatabaseType postgresql
  }
}
Only use keys you need; invalid keys break import.
